21/11/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The Serbian Parliament voted on Friday (19 November) to adopt the republic's 2005 budget.
Revenue from taxes, foreign loans, donations, the sale of state-run companies and government bonds are expected to amount to 5.2 billion euros, while the projected spending will be 5.4 billion euros.
Inflation is forecast at 9.1 per cent, down from this year's 11 per cent.
Finance Minister Mladjan Dinkic told lawmakers that the government is forecasting economic growth of 4 per cent to 5 per cent.
He also unveiled plans for cuts in public spending and tax breaks for export-oriented companies.
(AP, AFP - 20/11/04)
